{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016rxMFpC6pveEPJyf49TrPS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Errors Subsystem Design\n3\tdate: 2026-04-30\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Canonical error-type ownership, binding mapping inputs, and corruption detail host file\n6\tblast_radius: fathomdb-engine errors; bindings; acceptance AC-035* and AC-060*\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Errors Design\n11\t\n12\tThis file is the design owner named by `architecture.md` for the cross-cutting\n13\terror surface.\n14\t\n15\t## Top-level types\n16\t\n17\t- `EngineError` owns post-open runtime failures returned by `write`, `search`,\n18\t  `close`, scheduler callbacks, and op-store validation on accepted 0.6.0\n19\t  write paths.\n20\t- `EngineOpenError` owns `Engine.open` failures, including lock contention,\n21\t  incompatible schema, embedder-identity mismatch, and corruption-on-open.\n22\t\n23\tBindings map these roots into language-idiomatic class hierarchies per\n24\t`design/bindings.md`.\n25\t\n26\tTop-level ownership boundary:\n27\t\n28\t- `design/engine.md` owns when open-path stages produce `EngineOpenError`.\n29\t- Subsystem design docs own the semantics of their module errors.\n30\t- This file owns which module errors stay distinct, which top-level root they\n31\t  route through, and the stable machine-readable payload fields bindings may\n32\t  depend on.\n33\t\n34\t## Module taxonomy\n35\t\n36\tPer ADR-0.6.0-error-taxonomy, per-module errors stay distinct when they carry\n37\tdifferent remediation or cross-doc ownership.\n38\t\n39\t| Error type                      | Produced by                                        | Routed through    | Semantics owner         | Why distinct                                                                    |\n40\t| ------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n41\t| `StorageError`                  | canonical SQLite read/write path                   | `EngineError`     | `design/engine.md`      | physical storage / transaction failures are not projection or op-store failures |\n42\t| `ProjectionError`               | projection-row commit / terminal-state accounting  | `EngineError`     | `design/projections.md` | projection freshness and failure-state rules are distinct from canonical writes |\n43\t| `VectorError`                   | `sqlite-vec` encode/load/query path                | `EngineError`     | `design/vector.md`      | vector capability / encoding failures have vector-specific recovery             |\n44\t| `EmbedderError`                 | embedder dispatch, timeout, invalid vector return  | `EngineError`     | `design/embedder.md`    | caller remediation is \"fix or replace embedder,\" not \"retry generic write\"      |\n45\t| `SchedulerError`                | scheduler startup/shutdown / queue orchestration   | `EngineError`     | `design/scheduler.md`   | queue and shutdown failures are not vector math or write-shape failures         |\n46\t| `OpStoreError`                  | unknown collection, kind mismatch, registry misuse | `EngineError`     | `design/op-store.md`    | op-store contract failures are separate from primary graph writes               |\n47\t| `WriteValidationError`          | malformed typed write shape                        | `EngineError`     | `design/engine.md`      | fix caller-submitted field shape / variant construction                         |\n48\t| `SchemaValidationError`         | JSON Schema rejection for op-store payloads        | `EngineError`     | `design/op-store.md`    | fix payload contents against registered `schema_id`                             |\n49\t| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError` | open-time stored-vs-supplied identity comparison   | `EngineOpenError` | `design/embedder.md`    | open-time incompatibility, not runtime write/query failure                      |\n50\t| `MigrationError`                | schema migration execution                         | `EngineOpenError` | `design/migrations.md`  | open-time schema transition failure with per-step reporting                     |\n51\t\n52\t`Overloaded` and `Closing` remain direct `EngineError` variants rather than\n53\tmodule errors because they are cross-cutting runtime states:\n54\t\n55\t- `OverloadedError`\n56\t- `ClosingError`\n57\t\n58\tThis file is the canonical home for the variant-to-binding mapping inputs and\n59\tthe reason the named error modules exist at all.\n60\t\n61\t## Validation boundary\n62\t\n63\tThe validation split is load-bearing and must not be collapsed in owner docs or\n64\tbindings:\n65\t\n66\t- `WriteValidationError` means the submitted typed write is malformed before\n67\t  schema-sensitive payload checks run.\n68\t- `SchemaValidationError` means the op-store payload is structurally valid JSON\n69\t  but fails the registered `schema_id` JSON Schema at save time.\n70\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError` is not a write-time validation at all; it is\n71\t  an open-time compatibility failure.\n72\t\n73\t`design/engine.md`, `design/op-store.md`, `design/bindings.md`, and\n74\t`acceptance.md` must preserve this split.\n75\t\n76\t## Binding mapping ownership\n77\t\n78\tThis file owns the stable inputs bindings map from:\n79\t\n80\t- top-level root (`EngineError` vs `EngineOpenError`)\n81\t- module / direct variant identity\n82\t- stable machine payload fields\n83\t\n84\t`design/bindings.md` owns the mapping protocol:\n85\t\n86\t- one class per variant\n87\t- single rooted hierarchy per binding\n88\t- typed attributes rather than message parsing\n89\t\n90\t`interfaces/{python,ts,cli}.md` own idiomatic casing and concrete class names.\n91\t\n92\t## Binding-facing class matrix\n93\t\n94\tThe matrix below is the canonical cross-binding class-stem table for 0.6.0.\n95\tPer-language interface docs may apply idiomatic casing, but they must not\n96\trename the semantic class stems or collapse distinct rows.\n97\t\n98\t| Rust-side surface                | Python class stem                | TypeScript class stem            | CLI dispatch class    |\n99\t| -------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | --------------------- |\n100\t| `StorageError`                   | `StorageError`                   | `StorageError`                   | runtime failure       |\n101\t| `ProjectionError`                | `ProjectionError`                | `ProjectionError`                | runtime failure       |\n102\t| `VectorError`                    | `VectorError`                    | `VectorError`                    | runtime failure       |\n103\t| `EmbedderError`                  | `EmbedderError`                  | `EmbedderError`                  | runtime failure       |\n104\t| `SchedulerError`                 | `SchedulerError`                 | `SchedulerError`                 | runtime failure       |\n105\t| `OpStoreError`                   | `OpStoreError`                   | `OpStoreError`                   | runtime failure       |\n106\t| `WriteValidationError`           | `WriteValidationError`           | `WriteValidationError`           | runtime failure       |\n107\t| `SchemaValidationError`          | `SchemaValidationError`          | `SchemaValidationError`          | runtime failure       |\n108\t| `Overloaded`                     | `OverloadedError`                | `OverloadedError`                | runtime failure       |\n109\t| `Closing`                        | `ClosingError`                   | `ClosingError`                   | runtime failure       |\n110\t| `DatabaseLocked`                 | `DatabaseLockedError`            | `DatabaseLockedError`            | lock-held             |\n111\t| `Corruption(CorruptionDetail)`   | `CorruptionError`                | `CorruptionError`                | corruption            |\n112\t| `IncompatibleSchemaVersion`      | `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError` | `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError` | incompatible-schema   |\n113\t| `MigrationError`                 | `MigrationError`                 | `MigrationError`                 | migration-failed      |\n114\t| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | open mismatch         |\n115\t| `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | open/runtime mismatch |\n116\t\n117\tDecision note:\n118\t\n119\t- Python uses a single rooted hierarchy beneath one base class.\n120\t- TypeScript uses one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, with distinct\n121\t  open-time and runtime leaf classes beneath it.\n122\t- The leaf-class rows above are canonical regardless of whether TS ultimately\n123\t  groups open-time and runtime leaves in documentation.\n124\t\n125\t## Corruption detail owner\n126\t\n127\tThis file is the canonical host for the `CorruptionDetail` payload contract\n128\tcarried by `EngineOpenError::Corruption`:\n129\t\n130\t- `CorruptionKind`\n131\t- `OpenStage`\n132\t- `CorruptionLocator`\n133\t- `RecoveryHint.code`\n134\t- `RecoveryHint.doc_anchor`\n135\t\n136\t`design/engine.md` and `design/recovery.md` cite these rows by stable code and\n137\tmust not redeclare the same join in parallel.\n138\t\n139\t### Surface split\n140\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9bf016af-3b87-4a97-9dc2-e8a2161a09cc","uuid":"a13e4b28-7284-4f00-9f89-c4f9f15f5b7a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T18:52:13.366Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-11a-pyo3-binding-20260516T174849Z/dev/design/errors.md","content":"---\ntitle: Errors Subsystem Design\ndate: 2026-04-30\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Canonical error-type ownership, binding mapping inputs, and corruption detail host file\nblast_radius: fathomdb-engine errors; bindings; acceptance AC-035* and AC-060*\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Errors Design\n\nThis file is the design owner named by `architecture.md` for the cross-cutting\nerror surface.\n\n## Top-level types\n\n- `EngineError` owns post-open runtime failures returned by `write`, `search`,\n  `close`, scheduler callbacks, and op-store validation on accepted 0.6.0\n  write paths.\n- `EngineOpenError` owns `Engine.open` failures, including lock contention,\n  incompatible schema, embedder-identity mismatch, and corruption-on-open.\n\nBindings map these roots into language-idiomatic class hierarchies per\n`design/bindings.md`.\n\nTop-level ownership boundary:\n\n- `design/engine.md` owns when open-path stages produce `EngineOpenError`.\n- Subsystem design docs own the semantics of their module errors.\n- This file owns which module errors stay distinct, which top-level root they\n  route through, and the stable machine-readable payload fields bindings may\n  depend on.\n\n## Module taxonomy\n\nPer ADR-0.6.0-error-taxonomy, per-module errors stay distinct when they carry\ndifferent remediation or cross-doc ownership.\n\n| Error type                      | Produced by                                        | Routed through    | Semantics owner         | Why distinct                                                                    |\n| ------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `StorageError`                  | canonical SQLite read/write path                   | `EngineError`     | `design/engine.md`      | physical storage / transaction failures are not projection or op-store failures |\n| `ProjectionError`               | projection-row commit / terminal-state accounting  | `EngineError`     | `design/projections.md` | projection freshness and failure-state rules are distinct from canonical writes |\n| `VectorError`                   | `sqlite-vec` encode/load/query path                | `EngineError`     | `design/vector.md`      | vector capability / encoding failures have vector-specific recovery             |\n| `EmbedderError`                 | embedder dispatch, timeout, invalid vector return  | `EngineError`     | `design/embedder.md`    | caller remediation is \"fix or replace embedder,\" not \"retry generic write\"      |\n| `SchedulerError`                | scheduler startup/shutdown / queue orchestration   | `EngineError`     | `design/scheduler.md`   | queue and shutdown failures are not vector math or write-shape failures         |\n| `OpStoreError`                  | unknown collection, kind mismatch, registry misuse | `EngineError`     | `design/op-store.md`    | op-store contract failures are separate from primary graph writes               |\n| `WriteValidationError`          | malformed typed write shape                        | `EngineError`     | `design/engine.md`      | fix caller-submitted field shape / variant construction                         |\n| `SchemaValidationError`         | JSON Schema rejection for op-store payloads        | `EngineError`     | `design/op-store.md`    | fix payload contents against registered `schema_id`                             |\n| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError` | open-time stored-vs-supplied identity comparison   | `EngineOpenError` | `design/embedder.md`    | open-time incompatibility, not runtime write/query failure                      |\n| `MigrationError`                | schema migration execution                         | `EngineOpenError` | `design/migrations.md`  | open-time schema transition failure with per-step reporting                     |\n\n`Overloaded` and `Closing` remain direct `EngineError` variants rather than\nmodule errors because they are cross-cutting runtime states:\n\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nThis file is the canonical home for the variant-to-binding mapping inputs and\nthe reason the named error modules exist at all.\n\n## Validation boundary\n\nThe validation split is load-bearing and must not be collapsed in owner docs or\nbindings:\n\n- `WriteValidationError` means the submitted typed write is malformed before\n  schema-sensitive payload checks run.\n- `SchemaValidationError` means the op-store payload is structurally valid JSON\n  but fails the registered `schema_id` JSON Schema at save time.\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError` is not a write-time validation at all; it is\n  an open-time compatibility failure.\n\n`design/engine.md`, `design/op-store.md`, `design/bindings.md`, and\n`acceptance.md` must preserve this split.\n\n## Binding mapping ownership\n\nThis file owns the stable inputs bindings map from:\n\n- top-level root (`EngineError` vs `EngineOpenError`)\n- module / direct variant identity\n- stable machine payload fields\n\n`design/bindings.md` owns the mapping protocol:\n\n- one class per variant\n- single rooted hierarchy per binding\n- typed attributes rather than message parsing\n\n`interfaces/{python,ts,cli}.md` own idiomatic casing and concrete class names.\n\n## Binding-facing class matrix\n\nThe matrix below is the canonical cross-binding class-stem table for 0.6.0.\nPer-language interface docs may apply idiomatic casing, but they must not\nrename the semantic class stems or collapse distinct rows.\n\n| Rust-side surface                | Python class stem                | TypeScript class stem            | CLI dispatch class    |\n| -------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | --------------------- |\n| `StorageError`                   | `StorageError`                   | `StorageError`                   | runtime failure       |\n| `ProjectionError`                | `ProjectionError`                | `ProjectionError`                | runtime failure       |\n| `VectorError`                    | `VectorError`                    | `VectorError`                    | runtime failure       |\n| `EmbedderError`                  | `EmbedderError`                  | `EmbedderError`                  | runtime failure       |\n| `SchedulerError`                 | `SchedulerError`                 | `SchedulerError`                 | runtime failure       |\n| `OpStoreError`                   | `OpStoreError`                   | `OpStoreError`                   | runtime failure       |\n| `WriteValidationError`           | `WriteValidationError`           | `WriteValidationError`           | runtime failure       |\n| `SchemaValidationError`          | `SchemaValidationError`          | `SchemaValidationError`          | runtime failure       |\n| `Overloaded`                     | `OverloadedError`                | `OverloadedError`                | runtime failure       |\n| `Closing`                        | `ClosingError`                   | `ClosingError`                   | runtime failure       |\n| `DatabaseLocked`                 | `DatabaseLockedError`            | `DatabaseLockedError`            | lock-held             |\n| `Corruption(CorruptionDetail)`   | `CorruptionError`                | `CorruptionError`                | corruption            |\n| `IncompatibleSchemaVersion`      | `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError` | `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError` | incompatible-schema   |\n| `MigrationError`                 | `MigrationError`                 | `MigrationError`                 | migration-failed      |\n| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`  | open mismatch         |\n| `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError` | open/runtime mismatch |\n\nDecision note:\n\n- Python uses a single rooted hierarchy beneath one base class.\n- TypeScript uses one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, with distinct\n  open-time and runtime leaf classes beneath it.\n- The leaf-class rows above are canonical regardless of whether TS ultimately\n  groups open-time and runtime leaves in documentation.\n\n## Corruption detail owner\n\nThis file is the canonical host for the `CorruptionDetail` payload contract\ncarried by `EngineOpenError::Corruption`:\n\n- `CorruptionKind`\n- `OpenStage`\n- `CorruptionLocator`\n- `RecoveryHint.code`\n- `RecoveryHint.doc_anchor`\n\n`design/engine.md` and `design/recovery.md` cite these rows by stable code and\nmust not redeclare the same join in parallel.\n\n### Surface split\n","numLines":140,"startLine":1,"totalLines":217}}}
